{meta: title Ghost Riders In The Sky}
{meta: artist Johnny Cash}
{meta: writer Stan Jones}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[Am]An old cowboy went riding out one dark and windy [C]day
[Am]Upon a ridge he rested as he went along his way
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
When all at once a mighty herd of red-eyed cows he saw
[F]Plowing through the ragged skies  and up a cloudy [Am]draw
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[Am]Their brands were still on fire and their hooves were made of [C]steel
Their horns were black and shiny and their hot [Am]breath he could feel
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
A bolt of fear went through him as they thundered through the sky
For he saw [F]the riders coming hard  and he heard their mournful [Am]cry
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
Yipie [C]i-oh  Yipie [Am]i-ay    [F]ghost riders in the [Am]sky
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
[Am]Their faces gaunt their eyes were blurred
Their shirts all soaked with [C]sweat
He’s riding hard to catch that herd but he [Am]ain't caught 'em yet
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 7}
Cause they've got to ride forever on that range up in the sky
On [F]horses snorting fire  as they ride on hear their [Am]cry
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 8}
[Am]As the riders loped on by him he heard one call his [C]name
If you want to save your soul from hell a riding [Am]on our range
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 9}
Then cowboy change your ways today or with us you will ride
[F]Trying to catch the devil’s herd  across these endless [Am]skies
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 10}
Yipie [C]i-oh  Yipie [Am]i-ay   [F]ghost riders in the [Am]sky
[F]Ghost riders in the [Am]sky  
[F]Ghost riders in the [Am]sky
{end_of_verse}
